race.description: Red Capp Cleaning & Property Services Handicap (C1)
race.comment: ORLOVA (5) got off the mark in style three weeks ago and the rise to the mile looks ideal now. The form around her has already stood up with two subsequent winners emerging from that maiden, and she draws well again with the claimer staying aboard. She can absolutely go on with it. ROUSING REFRAIN (1) was also doing his best work late and went much better than the formguide suggests. He's peaking now and gets Holder. Genuine winning hope. HAMNER SPRINGS (6) keeps teasing without landing the blow, but he's doing enough to stay in the conversation again. BARGAIN BOY (2) was good without threatening in town last time and is rock-hard fit. Just needs some luck from the wide alley.
